issue.body:
Our projects can contain large models so we use compiled models to improve application startup.

We have models similar to the ones below:

```C#
public class PatientModel
{
    [DatabaseGenerated(DatabaseGeneratedOption.Identity)]
    public int Id { get; set; }

    public List<HumanName> Name { get; set; }

    public List<string> Address { get; set; }
}

[Owned]
public class HumanName
{
    public string Last { get; set; }

    public string[] Given { get; set; }
}
```

Below is a sample code querying the data using minimal api

```C#
app.MapPost("/Patient", async ([FromServices] PatientContext context, [FromBody] PatientModel patient) =>
{
    context.Patients.Add(patient);
    await context.SaveChangesAsync();
    return Results.Created($"/Patient/{patient.Id}", patient);
});

app.MapGet("/Patient", async ([FromServices] PatientContext context, [FromQuery] string? given, [FromQuery] string? name, [FromQuery] string? address) =>
{
    IQueryable<PatientModel> query = context.Patients;

    if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(given))
    {
        query = query.Where(x => x.Name.Any(y => y.Given.Contains(given)));
    }

    if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(name))
    {
        query = query.Where(x => x.Name.Any(y => y.Given.Any(z => z.StartsWith(name)) || y.Last.StartsWith(name)));
    }

    if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(address))
    {
        query = query.Where(x => x.Address.Any(y => y.StartsWith(address)));
    }

    var result = await query.ToListAsync();

    return result;
});
```

When not using compiled models, the queries successfully return data. But when we use compiled models, we get errors saying the LINQ expression could not be translated.

